## What is Wireshark?

Wireshark is a free, open-source network protocol analyser. It captures traffic passing through a network interface in real time and lets you inspect individual packets down to the byte level which protocol they use, where they're going and in the case of unencrypted traffic their actual contents.

## Installation

Installed through the official Windows installer from wireshark.org, which bundles **Npcap**, a packet capture driver required for Wireshark to see live traffic on Windows. Installation required administrator permissions to install the Npcap driver.

